  "texts": [
    "Notably, the TIG framework significantly outperformed all baseline methods across all evaluation metrics, demonstrating superior performance when integrated with Llama 2 as the knowledge generator.",
    "Importantly, our results were consistently the best regardless of the parameter size of the knowledge generator (Llama 2 7B, 13B or 70B), highlighting the robustness and effectiveness of our approach across different scales of the knowledge generator.For instance, our method with OPT 1.3B achieved the best overall results on the ComVE dataset, significantly outperforming the strongest baselines across all metrics.",
    "Specifically, compared to the best baseline on each metric, TIP's METEOR score was 192% higher, while its ROUGE score improved by 204%.",
    "Regarding BERTScore and Sent Bert, TIP outperformed the top baseline by 50%Furthermore, larger models like Llama 2 70B and Vicuna 33B demonstrated strong performance with our method but did not achieve the same level of improvement as OPT did when integrated with TIP framework.",
    "This is because their larger parameter sizes already provide them with substantial capabilities for handling complex tasks and reasoning, which means that the additional boost from our TIP framework, while beneficial, was not as pronounced as it was for the smaller OPT model.The CSE dataset, as shown in Table 3, further validated the effectiveness of our TIP framework."
